/*
    HDFS ESSENTIALS
*/

HDFS a file system that manages the storage of data 

    - Handles large datasets
    - Data replication 
    - High throughput
    - High availability

/*
    HDFS ARCHITECHTURE
*/

1 namenode : master server that manages the file system namespace, stores metadata, replica locations
n datanode : manages storage based on instuctions from namenode 
The replicas are stored in different data nodes

The file is broken into blocks of size 128 MB
/*
    HDFS COMMANDS
*/

hadoop fs -ls
    or
hdfs dfs -ls
hdfs dfs -mkdir
hdfs dfs -put
hdfs dfs -text
hdfs dfs -copyFromLocal <localFilePath> <hdfsPath>
